President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday signed a record N17.13 trillion 2022 appropriation bill into law at the state house in Abuja. The president also signed the 2021 finance bill into law. Among those present at the event were Ahmed Lawan, president of the senate; Femi Gbajabiamila, speaker of the house of representatives; Zainab Ahmed, minister of finance, budget, and national planning; Boss Mustapha, secretary to the government of the federation and Lai Mohammed, minister of information. Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo was absent at the ceremony. Below are photos. <img class="alignnone wp-image-645268" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET9.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="367" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET9.jpg 1080w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET9-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET9-24x16.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET9-36x24.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET9-48x32.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /> <img class="alignnone wp-image-645269" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET8.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="367" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET8.jpg 1080w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET8-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/BUHARI-SIGNS-2020-BUDGET8-1024x683.jpg 1024w, http